  "prompt": "Are there international laws against money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several international laws and regulations aimed at preventing money laundering:\n\n1. The Financial Action Task Force (FATF) sets global standards for combating money laundering and terrorist financing.\n\n2. The United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime provides guidelines for international cooperation.\n\n3. The Bank Secrecy Act (BSA) and the USA PATRIOT Act are key U.S. laws with international implications.\n\n4. The European Union's Anti-Money Laundering Directives establish regulations for member states.\n\n5. Many countries have their own national laws requiring financial institutions to report suspicious transactions and conduct customer due diligence.\n\nThese laws typically require financial institutions to:\n- Verify customer identities\n- Report suspicious transactions\n- Maintain transaction records\n- Implement compliance programs\n- Cooperate with law enforcement investigations\n\nPenalties for money laundering can include significant fines and criminal prosecution.",
